               <msContents>
                  <summary> This copy of the <title>Mas̲navī-i Ma‘navī</title> (Spiritual Couplets)
                     by <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/98930150" key="person_98930150">Jalāl
                        al-Dīn Rūmī (1207–1273)</persName> contains six illuminated headers
                     indicating the start of each of book within the volume. A scribe named
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" role="scr" key="person_f7852">Ni‘mat
                        Khān</persName> copied this volume over five months in <placeName
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083556" key="place_1083556">Kasur,
                        Punjab</placeName>, where he finished it on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">6
                        Rajab 1079 AH (10 Dec. 1688)</date>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/98930150" key="person_98930150">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī,
                           1207–1273</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">جلال الدین رومی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="com" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66900471" key="person_66900471">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Sulṭān Valad, 1226–1312</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName  xml:lang="fa">سلطان ولد</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <editor><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" role="scr" key="person_f7852">Ni‘mat
                           Khān</persName>; 
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">نعمت خان</persName></editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20506" change="#ids-cleanup"
                        >Mas̲navī-i Ma‘navī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20506" change="#ids-cleanup"> مثنوی
                        معنوی</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="beginning"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> بشنو از نی چون حکایت میکند * و ز جدأیها شکایت
                        میکند</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="334b" to="334b"> برگ ۳۳۴پ (folio
                           334b):</locus> ور سهو خطای با واقع * رب اغفر لي انکه <damage
                           xml:lang="fa">انت</damage> تواب </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="270b" to="270b"> برگ ۲۷۰پ (folio
                           270b):</locus> المشق فقیر عارضی نعمتخان </colophon>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="334b" to="334b"> برگ ۳۳۴پ (folio
                           334b):</locus> تمت تمام شد کتاب تصنیف مولوی صاحبی روم مسنوی المشق قفیر
                        حقیر احقر الناس نعمت خان متوطن قوم طرین سکي بتاریخ ششم ۶ رجب المرجب سنه ۱۰۷۹
                        جلوس میمون سنه ۱۲ در مدت پنج ماه مرقوم نموده شد و الله اعلم بالقوات. </colophon>
                     <colophon>Signed twice by the scribe <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                           role="scr" key="person_f7852">Ni‘mat Khān</persName>, briefly on folio
                           <locus from="270b" to="270b">270b</locus> and a full statement on folio
                           <locus from="334b" to="334b">334b</locus> which indicates that he copied
                        over a period of five months in <placeName type="town"
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083556" key="place_1083556">Kasur,
                           Punjab</placeName> in the <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                           when="1688-12-10">6 Rajab 1079 AH (10 Dec. 1688)</date>, <q>in the 12th
                           year of the august reign [of the Emperor ‘Ālamgīr I]</q>.</colophon>
                     <note>Former owner <persName role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66617580"
                           key="person_66617580">Duncan Forbes (1798–1868)</persName> mistakenly
                        describes the volume as completed in <q xml:lang="en">the reign of
                        Akbar</q>, but the date actually corresponds to that of <persName
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/6178410/" cert="high" key="person_6178410"
                           >‘Ālamgīr I</persName>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item1">
                        <locus from="1b" to="1b">1b</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book One</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر الاوّل</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Daftar-i Avval</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item2">
                        <locus from="53a" to="53a">53a</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book Two</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر دوّم</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Daftar-i Duvvum</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item3">
                        <locus from="101a" to="101a">101a</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book Three</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر سیوم</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"> Daftar-i Sīyūm</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item4">
                        <locus from="162b" to="162b">162b</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book Four</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر چهادم</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Daftar-i Chahārum</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item5">
                        <locus from="213b" to="213b">213b</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book Five</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر پنجم</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Daftar-i Panjum</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_848-item1-item6">
                        <locus from="271b" to="271b">271b</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Book Six</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">دفتر ششم</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Daftar-i Shīshum</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <note>For other copies of this work held in the Rylands, see <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6652"><idno>Persian
                           MS 17</idno></ref>, <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6691">21</ref>,
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7223"
                           >72</ref>, <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6695"
                              >213</ref>, <ref
                                 target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6720">236</ref>,
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6736"
                           >250–255</ref> (Books I–VI), <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7301">795</ref>,
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7356"
                           >847</ref>, <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7438"
                           >926</ref>, <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26583">983</ref> (Book I), and <ref
                                 target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26584">984</ref>, the last being the earliest, completed in <date cert="high"
                                    calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1357-01-02">9 Muḥarram 758 AH (2 January
                                    1357 CE)</date>, about 85 years after the author first composed it. For critical editions, see Isti‘lāmī and
                        Furūzānfar. For a recent English translation of the first two books based on
                        the former edition, see Williams. For earlier translations, see Arberry,
                        Nicholson, and Whinfield.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Written on thin, cross-grained, ivory-coloured, externally sized
                           and polished <material>paper</material>, probably handmade in the
                              <placeName cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                              >Indian subcontinent</placeName>, with >1 mm. between laid lines and
                           few discernible chain lines.</support>
                        <extent><measure unit="folios" quantity="334"> 334 folios, 4 flyleaves (ff.
                              ii + 334 + ii)</measure>. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>272</height>
                              <width>165</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>187</height>
                              <width>101</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation> Originally foliated in pencilled partially-legible Arabic numerals
                           on the upper-left corners of the a sides that subsequently suffered mould
                           damage and also many trimmed off when rebound, therefore pencilled
                           foliation at top-left of the a sides in new Arabic numerals added when
                           catalogued. Former owner <persName role="fmo"
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66617580" key="person_66617580">Duncan
                              Forbes (1798–1868)</persName> describes the volume as having <q
                              xml:lang="en">663 pages</q> but it actually contains 4 more. </foliation>
                        <collation>Collation undetermined due to tight opening, but primarily
                           quaternions throughout. <catchwords>Catchwords present at the lower-left
                              corners of the b sides.</catchwords></collation>
                        <condition>Handle with caution. In fair condition, with extensive cut-outs
                           and infills on the margins repairs to inner quires in the gutters.
                           Extensive mould and damp damage throughout left the centres of many pages
                           weakened, with breaks and losses in the final folios.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1 4" ruledLines="21" n="mistara">Written in 1 to 4 columns
                           with 21 lines per page. Ruled with a <hi rend="italic">misṭarah</hi> hand
                           guide.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="naskh" medium="ink"> Primarily written in
                        nasta‘līq script in <material>black</material> with headers in
                           <material>red</material> by <persName role="scr" key="person_f7852"
                           >Ni‘mat Khān</persName>, who possibly also wrote some marginal notes
                        outlined in the same manner as the marginal ruling. </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscription:</label> Folio <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> inscribed
                     by <persName role="fmo"> Muḥammad Quṭb al-Dīn bin Hājjī Muḥammad
                        Aḥmad</persName> below his seal dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                        notBefore="1667" notAfter="1668">1178 AH (1667–68 CE)</date>, impressed over
